# Enforce LF line endings + byte-identical checkouts across platforms.
# Without this, Windows runners get CRLF-converted text files (notably
# `generated/plenum_bundle.js` and the polyfills) which gives them a
# different SHA than the Linux/macOS runners that produced the
# committed plugin sidecar — `afterburner-wasi/build.rs`'s drift gate
# then panics on a phantom mismatch.

# Default: text files normalize on commit, check out with LF.
*               text=auto eol=lf

# Generated assets that get hashed by build scripts MUST be byte-stable.
crates/afterburner-node-compat/generated/plenum_bundle.js text eol=lf
crates/afterburner-node-compat/polyfills/**            text eol=lf
crates/afterburner-wasi/plugin/afterburner_plugin.wasm.bundle-sha256 text eol=lf

# Binary artifacts — never touch.
*.wasm          binary
*.png           binary
*.svg           binary
*.mp4           binary
*.zip           binary
*.tar.gz        binary

# Shell scripts: explicit LF so Windows-checked-out copies still
# `chmod +x` cleanly when run via WSL / git-bash.
*.sh            text eol=lf
*.ps1           text eol=crlf
